Package de.tub.pes.syscir.sc_model

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    SCVariable
    the Interface of a variable to combine all types of variables
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    SCFunction
    represents a SystemC-Function with a name, a list of parameters, a returntype, a list of expressions which represents the body of the function and a lsit of variables which are declared inside the function
    SCModule
    this represents a SystemC-Module, it contains variables, functions, a constructor, a list of fathers and a marker if its a channel or not, it inherits these parts from SCStruct it also contains a list of ports an sockets, a list of processes, a list of moduleInstances and a List of events
    SCPortSCSocket
    this class represents the ports and sockets in systemC it have an name, a connectiontype and a type.
    SCPortSCSocketInstance
    this class represents an instance of a port or socket an instance is symbolized by the port and an Instance of a Module it also has lists of connected Channelsm in case of a port, or a list of other portsocketinstances in case of a socket
    SCProcess
    this class represents a SCProcess it has a Link to a SCFunction, a List of Events on which this process is sensitive for and en enumSet of Modifiers theirs also a nam, which ist usualy equal to the function-name an a Type, for example SCThread, SCMethod
    SCStruct
    this represents a SystemC-Struct, it contains variables, functions, a constructor, a list of fathers and a marker if its a channel or not
    SCSystem
